---

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
On this day, I learned how to apply **Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)** concepts in Python by building a **Coffee Machine** program.  

- The coffee machine has limited resources (water, milk, coffee).  
- The user can choose a drink (espresso, latte, cappuccino).  
- The machine checks if resources are sufficient.  
- The user inserts coins, and the machine processes the transaction.  
- Resources update after each purchase.  

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Concepts Practiced
- Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)  
- Creating and using classes  
- Methods, attributes, and constructors (`__init__`)  
- Interacting between multiple classes  
- Using procedural logic with OOP design  

